main event: Several unidentified objects were observed in the sky over Columbus, Ohio on July 28, 1956.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a balloon and at an estimated altitude of several hundred feet.
The objects' speed varied from stationary to very fast.
The duration of the sighting was 15 different minutes.
The objects did not fit the description of a standard aircraft.
The conclusion was that the objects were unidentified, and possibly astronomical in nature.
